ing Team,\r\n \r\nI am a hardworking and confident individual. I have completed my Bachelor\'s in Business Administration with an overall CGPA of 3.26. I have done my internship at Concord Group of Companies. As an HR major student, I have gathered in-depth knowledge of all the functions of HR, from recruitment to benefits. For example, I can make you a JD, I know about selection methods and how it works, I can do the calculation of Payslip, I know all the stages of Payroll and how to increase Employee Satisfaction, Engagement of Employees with Encouraging Creative Ideas. I\'ve also done my minor in Media studies & journalism, so I know Public Relations, Campaign Management, Promotions, etc. Other than the academic learning, I\'ve been involved with my university\'s various club activity through that journey I have gained much knowledge of various skills such as Communication, Organizing, Time Management, Networking, Decision Making, Problem Solving, etc.\r\n\r\nDuring my four years at ULAB, I’ve been able to manage my academic and extra-curriculum life at the same pace. I was elected as the Vice president of our creative & literature society. There I have gathered knowledge on how to organize an event and how to handle so many people and tasks at the same time. Besides that, as I enjoy expanding my learning, I have proficient knowledge in MS Office, Google Suite, and other software like Lightroom and Adobe Illustrator. I have also taken part in different leadership programs and competitions. \r\n\r\nI have one year of working experience at EMK Center as an envoy. The position was under the communication officer. It was a part-time job. Through this journey, I have learned a lot directly from a professional platform. This experience has built me as a strong individual and expanded my knowledge on various subjects. I got the opportunity to communicate with different ages of people and discuss with them several important social topics. It has helped me to grow my skills in communication, public speaking, team collaboration, leadership, etc. Lastly, I would like to share my volunteering experience. This year I got the privilege to represent my country at an international platform named “Movers Programme”. It is a project by UNDP & Youth Co: lab. It is made to encourage youths to take actions for their community by learning about the SDGs & Social Entrepreneurship. And here my role is to facilitate workshops where young people can learn about SDGs & Social Entrepreneurship.\r\n\r\nI believe I will make an excellent addition to your team. This job opportunity will help me grow my real-world experience in the corporate industry.', 'B.B.A', '3.26', '{\"1\":{\"achieve\":\"Completed \\u201cBright Network Internship Experience UK\\u201d as a Consultant Intern.\"},\"2\":{\"achieve\":\"Attended as a participant in an international Summit named \\u201cResilient Youth Leadership Summit\\u201d organized by Islamic Cooperation Youth Forum (ICYF), Ministry of Youth & Sports of the People\\u2019s Republic Bangladesh, and Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People\\u2019s Republic Bangladesh\"},\"3\":{\"achieve\":\"Participated in \\u201cResilient Youth Leadership Bootcamp\\u201d organized by the University of Cambridge and Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People\\u2019s Republic Bangladesh\"},\"4\":{\"achieve\":\"Awarded as a Bronze Awardee at Duke of Edinburgh Award 2019\"},\"5\":{\"achieve\":\"Competed in \\u201cInsignia\'19: A Business Quiz Competition held in Kolkata (India)\\u201d\"},\"6\":{\"achieve\":\"Elected as a Publication Secretary of Paper Canoe: ULAB Literary Society\"},\"7\":{\"achieve\":\"Organized \\u201cYouth pen of Thoughts 2019: a writing summit\\u201d, collaborated with Paper Canoe: ULAB Literary Society and Dhaka FM 90.4\"},\"8\":{\"achieve\":\"Assigned as an Event Manager in ULAB Co-curricular Fest 2019\"},\"9\":{\"achieve\":\"Ranked 6th in an Online Photography Contest organized by Dhaka University Environment Society (